Package gui

The graphical user interface for the shortest paths algorithm (you don't need to look at or understand this package, but you can run it to play with the gui). Running the Main class well let you test your shortest paths algorithm on a randomly generated graph. If you would prefer to load a specific graph from a file, you can edit the run configuration in eclipse (the little arrow next to the run button) and add the filename to the "arguments" box.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Colorable
    A colorable object is an object that has a color field.
    Getting the color should be open, but setting it is protected, so
    setting the color can be done only by the game files.
    GraphElement
    Interface GraphElement can be implemented by any class that wants to be drawn on the GUI.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Adapter  
    Circle
    Graphics class Circle allows the drawing of circles.
    Circles use an (x1, y1, diameter) coordinate system of where they are located
    on the board.
    Each Circle is tied to and represents a BoardElement.
    DPoint
    An instance is a point (x, y)
    DraggableCircle
    An instance is a circle that can be dragged by the user on the gui
    EdgeData
    Class Edge allows creation of connections between Nodes.
    Each Edge is bidirectional and is connected to exactly two Nodes.
    Graph
    An instance contains HashSets of Edges and Nodes that make up the graph.
    GUI
    An instance is the JFrame that shows the graph.
    Class graph.Main and perhaps other classes send updates to the gui
    to keep it up to date on the graph state.
    The user has no interaction with class GUI.
    Line
    This graphics class allows the drawing of lines.
    Lines use a (c1, c2) coordinate system, where c1 and c2 are circle objects
    that denote the endpoints of this line.
    Each circle has (x, y) coordinates, so a Line can be though of as having
    (x1, y1, x2, y2).
    Each Line is tied to a BoardElement (most likely an Edge) that it represents.
    Main
    Game starting methods.
    NodeData
    A Node (vertex) of the graph.
    TextIO
    This class enables reading and writing text from/to a file.
